# AM FMEA — Failure Mode, Effects & Criticality Analysis
## Multi-Station Packaging Line

## Purpose
FMEA identifies potential
failure modes for each station, their effects, and their criticality, to
prioritize preventive maintenance and design improvements before failures
occur in production.

## Criticality scoring method
Criticality (C) = Severity (S) × Occurrence (O) × Detection (D), each scored
1-5 (5 = worst). Higher C score = higher priority for preventive action.

## FMEA table — representative stations
| Station | Failure Mode | Effect | S | O | D | C (S×O×D) | Recommended Action |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| Station 1 (Load) | Sensor misalignment | Missed part detection, jam | 3 | 3 | 2 | 18 | Include sensor alignment in weekly PM check |
| Station 1 (Load) | Actuator wear (pneumatic cylinder) | Slow/failed cycle, line stoppage | 4 | 2 | 3 | 24 | Add cylinder inspection to PM schedule; monitor cycle time trend |
| Station 2 (Pack) | Transfer misalignment (coupling wear) | Product damage, jam | 4 | 3 | 2 | 24 | Periodic alignment check per `mechanical-installation-procedure.md` tolerances |
| Station 2 (Pack) | Drive motor overload | Unplanned stoppage | 4 | 2 | 2 | 16 | Monitor amperage trend via VFD; verify load hasn't increased over time |
| Station 3 (Seal) | Seal head temperature drift | Poor seal quality (product/food-safety risk) | 5 | 3 | 3 | 45 | Highest priority: add temperature verification to PM; consider automated monitoring |
| Station 3 (Seal) | Fault sensor failure (no fault indication) | Undetected fault propagates downstream | 4 | 2 | 4 | 32 | Periodic sensor function test, not just visual inspection |

## How this drives the maintenance program
The highest-criticality items (Station 3 seal temperature, Station 2
transfer alignment) should be prioritized in the PM schedule ahead of
lower-criticality items — this is the link between AMDEC analysis and the
PM frequency decisions in `PM-schedule-template.md`
(`preventive-corrective-maintenance-program` repo).

## Link CMMS
In prthese FMEA priorities would be reflected as PM task frequency
and priority flags inside the CMMS (see `gmao-cmms-implementation.md` in the
`automation-plc-motor-control` repo) — high-criticality items get shorter PM
intervals and are flagged for immediate work order generation on any
anomaly, rather than waiting for the next scheduled round.

